ltiple%20audio%20channels%20for%20surround%20sound.%20These%20channels%20refer%20to%20how%20many%20directions%20sound%20can%20be%20sent%20through%20the%20device.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEntry-level%20soundbars%20often%20support%20two%20channels%20for%20basic%20left%20and%20right%20stereo%20playback%2C%20but%20many%20midrange%20and%20high-end%20models%20can%20support%20surround%20sound%20with%20five%20or%20more%20channels.%20These%20channels%20generally%20include%20a%20center%20channel%20for%20dialogue%20and%20rear%20channels%20via%20extra%20audio%20drivers%2C%20satellite%20speakers%2C%20or%20virtualization%20techniques.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChannel%20specifications%20are%20listed%20as%20a%20string%20of%20up%20to%20three%20numbers%20separated%20by%20decimal%20points.%20The%20first%20number%20represents%20how%20many%20standard%20ear-level%20channels%20are%20included%20(left%2C%20right%2C%20center%2C%20surrounds).%20The%20second%20number%20indicates%20if%20the%20device%20includes%20a%20dedicated%20low-frequency%20channel%20or%20separate%20subwoofer%20for%20extra%20bass.%20The%20final%20number%20indicates%20how%20many%20height%20channels%20are%20included%20for%20Dolby%20Atmos%20support.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBuyers%20who%20just%20want%20a%20simple%20upgrade%20from%20their%20TV's%20integrated%20audio%20will%20likely%20be%20satisfied%20with%20a%20compact%202.0%20or%202.1%20soundbar%20system.%20But%20if%20you're%20looking%20for%20a%20more%20complete%20home%20theater%20experience%2C%20you'll%20want%20to%20opt%20for%20a%205.1%20surround%20sound%20system%20or%20above.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20more%20recommendations%2C%20check%20out%20our%20complete%20guide%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fbest-surround-sound-systems%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebest%20surround%20sound%20systems%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20is%20Dolby%20Atmos%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EDolby%20Atmos%20is%20an%20immersive%20surround%20sound%20format%20that%20uses%20object-based%20audio%20mixing.%20In%20practice%2C%20this%20means%20that%20sounds%20can%20be%20more%20precisely%20positioned%20around%20your%20room%2C%20with%20effects%20placed%20in%20all%20directions%2C%20including%20overhead.%20For%20instance%2C%20when%20rain%20falls%20from%20the%20sky%2C%20or%20a%20helicopter%20flies%20overhead%2C%20you%20can%20actually%20hear%20the%20sound%20coming%20from%20above.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDolby%20Atmos%20soundbars%20can%20use%20one%20of%20two%20methods%20to%20create%20overhead%20sound%20effects.%20The%20first%20involves%20audio%20processing%20to%20create%20a%20simulated%20sense%20of%20height%20from%20regular%20ear-level%20speakers.%20The%20second%20method%20uses%20up-firing%20drivers%20angled%20up%20instead%20of%20forward%20to%20bounce%20sound%20effects%20off%20your%20ceiling.%20Generally%2C%20good%20up-firing%20drivers%20provide%20a%20much%20more%20convincing%20sense%20of%20overhead%20sound%20than%20audio%20processing%20can%20produce%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20more%20specifics%2C%20see%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fwhat-is-dolby-atmos%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWhat%20is%20Dolby%20Atmos%3C%2Fa%3E%20explainer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EDo%20I%20need%20a%20subwoofer%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EA%20subwoofer%20can%20be%20an%20integral%20part%20of%20your%20cinematic%20and%20musical%20experience.%20Due%20to%20basic%20physics%2C%20soundbars%20alone%20can't%20offer%20the%20deep%20bass%20frequencies%20you'd%20get%20from%20a%20subwoofer.%20If%20you're%20looking%20for%20earth-rattling%20thunder%2C%20hefty%20boom%20from%20explosions%2C%20and%20powerful%20bass%20beats%2C%20you'll%20want%20to%20consider%20a%20soundbar%20that%20either%20includes%20a%20subwoofer%20or%2C%20at%20the%20very%20least%2C%20allows%20you%20to%20add%20one%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20our%20top%20recommendations%2C%20check%20out%20our%20guide%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%