e.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20said%2C%20'We've%20got%20to%20change%20it.%20We're%20here%20for%20customers%2C'%26quot%3B%20he%20recalled.%20%26quot%3BObviously%2C%20I%20care%20about%20morale%20%E2%80%94%20but%20morale%20sucks%20because%20we%20suck.%20Morale%20will%20get%20better%20when%20we're%20better%20as%20a%20company.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20yet%20another%20lesson%2C%20Dimon%20encouraged%20leaders%20to%20push%20back%20against%20tropes%20like%20%26quot%3Bthat's%20the%20way%20we've%20always%20done%20it%26quot%3B%20to%20justify%20misguided%20decisions.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20important%20for%20leadership%20to%20always%20question%20what%20their%20company%20does%20and%20why%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%20The%20criticism%20comes%20amid%20a%20company-wide%20crackdown%2C%20led%20by%20Dimon%2C%20on%20bureaucracy%20and%20inefficiencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20illustrate%20his%20point%2C%20Dimon%20recalled%20dismissing%20a%20battalion%20of%20500%20management%20coaches%20the%20firm%20had%20been%20outsourcing.%20He%20cut%20the%20expense%20shortly%20after%20he%20joined%20JPMorgan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLots%20of%20times%20bad%20habits%20form%20and%20people%20get%20lazy%2C%20take%20shortcuts%20or%20don't%20care%20enough%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BI%20did%20it%20because%20it's%20a%20leader's%20job%20to%20coach%2C%20and%20we%20basically%20had%20outsourced%20management%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added%2C%20explaining%20his%20rationale.%20%26quot%3BIn%20my%20entire%20career%2C%20I've%20rarely%20seen%20this%20kind%20of%20outsourcing%20of%20responsibility%20succeed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDimon%20also%20said%20that%20a%20life%20of%20all%20work%20and%20no%20play%20risks%20leaving%20a%20person%20dull.%20Our%20jobs%2C%20he%20says%2C%20should%20still%20be%20enjoyable%2C%20even%20when%20we%20need%20to%20confront%20big%20challenges%20or%20own%20unpopular%20decisions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20spend%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20our%20waking%20hours%20at%20work%2C%26quot