w%20heaviest%20rocket%20fire%20by%20Hamas%20in%20months%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1744025316000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F3719%2Flive%2F77ee8940-139d-11f0-ac9f-c37d6fd89579.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fc0jzgp947qdo%231%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20journalist%20is%20reportedly%20killed%20in%20a%20strike%20at%20a%20hospital%20compound%20after%2010%20rockets%20are%20fired%20into%20Israel.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A183%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fc0jzgp947qdo%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fc0jzgp947qdo.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fc0jzgp947qdo.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20No%2C%20Satyajit%20Ray%20Is%20Not%20Your%20'Renaissance%20Man'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EAsk%20any%20scholar%20of%20world%20cinema%2C%20and%20you%20will%20know%20how%20widely%20and%20globally%20recognised%20Satyajit%20Ray's%20cinematic%20genius%20is.%20However%2C%20his%20career%20in%20India%E2%80%94living%20and%20posthumous%E2%80%94is%20a%20complex%20matter.%20It%20reveals%20a%20lot%20about%20Indian%20society%20and%20the%20structures%20that%20constitute%20its%20state%20apparatuses.%20Like%20many%20other%20stalwarts%20of%20his%20time%20and%20later%2C%20Ray's%20artistic%20legacy%20has%20been%20assimilated%2C%20tempered%2C%20and%2C%20often%2C%20even%20censored%20beyond%20recognition%20by%20the%20very%20institutions%20that%20appear%20to%20celebrate%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERay%2C%20who%20was%20awarded%20the%20Bharat%20Ratna%20in%201992%20-%20a%20month%20before%20his%20demise%20-%20had%20the%20distinction%20of%20seeing%20his%20documentary%20film%C2%A0%3Cem%3ESikkim%20%3C%2Fem%3E(1971)%20being%20banned%20by%20the%20government.%20A%20clear%20look%20into%20Ray's%20life%20and%20works%20reveals%20that%20the%20same%20political%2C%20cultural%2C%20and%20ideological%20frameworks%20that%20he%20often%20deconstructed%20in%20his%20cinema%20have%20contributed%20a%20great%20deal%20to%20the%20mythmaking%20surrounding%20his%20posthumous%20existence.%20And%20even%20though%20much%20of%20that%20mythology%20seems%20laudatory%2C%20one%20can't%20be%20sure%20whether%20Ray%20would%20have%20approved.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E'A%20Bureaucratic%20Invention'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERay's%20status%20as%20a%20harbinger%20of%20what%20was%20described%20in%20his%20last%20months%20as%20an%20%E2%80%98Indian%20Renaissance'%20wasn't%20entirely%20uncontested.%20Mercifully%20so!%20In%201992%2C%20a%20few%20months%20after%20Ray's%20demise%2C%20Utpal%20Dutt%20delivered%20a%20seminar%20commemorating%20his%20colleague's%20craftsmanship%20and%20ethical%20commitments.%20Among%20other%20things%2C%20Dutt%20mounted%20a%20scathing%20critique%20of%20the%20invisible%20nexus%20a%20few%C2%A0opportunistic%20elements%20of%20the%20Indian%20state%20and%20the%20cultural%20imperialism%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98West'.%20As%20Dutt%20reminded%20us%2C%20despite%20Ray's%20global%20acclaim%2C%20his%20film%20%3Cem%3ETeen%20Kanya%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1961)%2C%20adapted%20from%20Rabindranath%20Tagore's%20short%20stories%2C%20was%20distilled%20down%20to%20%3Cem%3ETwo%20Daughters%3C%2Fem%3E%20for%20state%20television.%20An%20audience%20mature%20enough%20was%20deemed%20unfit%20to%20understand%20the%20emotional%20or%20intellectual%20maturity%20the%20original%20film%20demanded.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20still%20from%20Teen%20Kanya%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22A%20still%20from%20Teen%20Kanya%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-04%2Fmsrrqah_teen-kanya_625x300_07_April_25.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20still%20from%20%3Cem%3ETeen%20Kanya%20%3C%2Fem%3E(1961)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBesides%2C%20Dutt%20was%20particularly%20troubled%20by%20the%20idea%20of%20Ray%20being%20a%20%E2%80%98Renaissance'%20man.%20He%20dismissed%20it%20as%20a%20bureaucratic%20invention%20lacking%20historical%20sincerity.%20Far%20from%20finding%20flaws%20in%20Ray's%20work%20and%20legacy%2C%20Dutt%20saw%20the%20title%20as%20compensation%20for%20the%20negligence%20doled%20out%20to%20his%20colleague%20during%20his%20lifetime.%C2%A0%20Though%20not%20a%20historian%20himself%2C%20Dutt's%20analysis%20was%20impeccable.%20He%20contrasted%20the%20so-called%20%E2%80%98renaissance'%20with%20the%20more%20historically%20sanguine%20%E2%80%98Bengal%20Renaissance'.%20The%20latter%2C%20unlike%20its%20purported%20%E2%80%98national'%20counterpart%2C%20arose%20in%20the%20early%2019th%20century%20out%20of%20palpable%20social%2C%20political%2C%20cultural%2C%20and%20ethical%20obligations%20-%20especially%20within%20and%20in%20opposition%20to%20a%20British%20regime.%20Transplanting%20that%20label%20onto%20Ray's%20posthumous%20specter%20was%20not%20just%20misleading%2C%20according%20to%20Dutt%2C%20but%20also%20politically%20manipulative%20as%20it%20sought%20to%20retrospectively%20reclaim%20Ray%20after%20the%20West%20had%20already%20validated%20his%20contributions%20through%20an%20honorary%20Oscar.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20some%20of%20India's%20state%20apparatuses%20were%20happy%20to%20ignore%20Ray%20until%20Hollywood%20-%20which%20itself%20was%20exposed%20to%20Ray's%20oeuvre%20only%20superficially%20-%20made%20it%20impossible%20for%20audiences%20back%20home%20to%20look%20the%20other%20way.%20The%20posthumous%20glorification%20his%20image%20underwent%20was%2C%20by%20no%20means%2C%20unique.%20It%20symptomised%20a%20larger%20institutional%20malaise%20in%20selectively%20supporting%20intellectuals%2C%20artists%2C%20scholars%2C%20and%20creative%20geniuses.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20People%20Who%20Didn't%20Care%20For%20Ray%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERecently%2C%20India's%20political%20leaders%20made%20headlines%20by%20debating%20what%20constituted%20the%20concept%20of%20a%20%E2%80%98state'.%20It%20was%20eventually%20concluded%20-%20somewhat%20churlishly%20and%20belatedly%20-%20that%20%E2%80%98state'%20comprises%20not%20only%20the%20ruling%20establishment%20but%20also%20the%20opposition.%20More%20significantly%2C%20as%20teachers%20of%20sociology%20and%20civic%20sciences%20will%20inform%20us%2C%20it%20also%20comprises%20various%20governmental%20and%20nongovernmental%20institutions%20that%20directly%20or%20indirectly%20collaborate%20in%20the%20nation%20state's%20functioning.%20In%20that%20comprehensive%20sense%2C%20even%20%E2%80%98We%2C%20the%20People'%20constitute%20the%20nation-state%20of%20India%2C%20that%20is%20Bharat.%20This%20clarification%20is%20important%20in%20Ray's%20context%20because%20a%20bulk%20of%20the%20apathy%20and%20misinterpretations%20directed%20towards%20him%20did%20not%20come%20from%20state%20actors%20but%20social%20structures.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20done%20in%20the%20guise%20of%20a%20seemingly%20sophisticated%20but%20actually%20lazy%20objection.%20Some%20listless%20critics%20suggested%20that%20Ray's%20cinema%20looked%20apolitical.%20Accordingly%2C%20it%20was%20driven%20by%20humanist%20concerns%2C%20not%20social%20or%20ideological%20acuity.%20It%20took%20his%20demise%20for%20that%20premise%20to%20be%20challenged.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20Chandak%20Sengoopta%20argues%2C%20Ray's%20films%20were%20ideologically%20layered%20and%20underpinned%20by%20anticolonial%20Bengali%20liberalism.%20Ray%20was%20not%20detached%20from%20the%20national%20discourse.%20Films%20like%20%3Cem%3EJalsaghar%20%3C%2Fem%3E(1958)%2C%20%3Cem%3ECharulata%20%3C%2Fem%3E(1964)%2C%20and%20%3Cem%3EShatranj%20Ke%20Khilari%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1977)%20were%20not%20just%20period%20dramas%20meant%20to%20nostalgically%20depict%20teakwood%2C%20boudoirs%2C%20artefacts%2C%20musical%20instruments%2C%20and%20knickknacks%20from%20nineteenth-century%20Calcutta%20and%20Lucknow.%20They%20confronted%20repressed%20questions%20of%20gendered%20private%20and%20public%20spaces%20and%20how%20old-fashioned%20coloniality%20affected%20postcolonial%20national%20subjects%2C%20whether%20male%2C%20female%2C%20anglicised%2C%20indigenised%2C%20libertarian%2C%20free-marketeer%2C%20or%20statist.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20still%20from%20Jalsaghar%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22A%20still%20from%20Jalsaghar%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-04%2Fgp4tk0jg_jalsaghar_625x300_07_April_25.jpg%3Fim%3DFaceCrop%2Calgorithm%3Ddnn%2Cwidth%3D1200%2Cheight%3D738%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20still%20from%20%3Cem%3EJalsaghar%20%3C%2Fem%3E(1958)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20one%20is%20not%20likely%20to%20find%20a%20direct%20feminist%20denunciation%20of%20patriarchal%20structures%20in%20Ray's%20critical%20oeuvre.%20But%2C%20as%20Devapriya%20Sanyal%20rightly%20adds%2C%20Ray's%20cinema%20was%20far%20more%20nuanced%2C%20in%20that%20it%20made%20men%20the%20bearers%20of%20the%20burden%20of%20being%20%E2%80%98national%20subjects'%20without%20leaving%20female%20characters%20out%20as%20irrelevant%3B%20he%20made%20them%20witnesses%20to%20the%20success%20or%20failure%20of%20their%20male%20counterparts%2C%20enfranchising%20them%20as%20the%20barometers%20of%20societal%20change.%20Simultaneously%2C%20as%20eloquently%20explained%20by%20Bishnupriya%20Ghosh%2C%20Ray's%20%E2%80%9Cpreoccupation%20with%20rural%20history%2C%20folk-cultures%20and%20religions%20of%20India%E2%80%9D%20only%20goes%20to%20underscore%20%E2%80%9Chis%20interest%20in%20articulating%20the%20non-western%20aspects%20of%20Indian%20culture%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnlike%20filmmakers%20committed%20to%20political%20activism%2C%20Ray%20did%20not%20rely%20on%20straightforward%20political%20staging%20to%20convey%20his%20ideology.%20Instead%2C%20he%20explored%20complex%20ideological%20interplays%20at%20locations%20where%20they%20truly%20manifest%20-%20the%20intimate%20lives%20of%20characters.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ERay's%20Nehruvian%20Beliefs%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERay%20was%20seen%2C%20erroneously%20of%20course%2C%20as%20being%20in%20alignment%20with%20Nehruvian%20developmental%20policies.%20That%20naturally%20led%20disengaged%20critics%20to%20think%20that%20someone%20of%20Ray's%20lineage%E2%80%94with%20Brahmo%20ideals%20and%20familial%20privilege%E2%80%94could%20only%20be%20too%20content%20with%20the%20fact%20of%20India's%20independence%20and%20an%20elite%20class's%20control%20over%20the%20nation's%20social%20and%20cultural%20capital.%20Brinda%20Bose%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20has%20in%20passing%20somewhat%20reaffirmed%20that%20Ray's%20early%20cinema%20%E2%80%98strongly%20endorsed%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru's%20vision%20of%20nation-building%2C%20which%20Ray%20greatly%20admired%20then'.%20Ray's%20%E2%80%98idealism'%2C%20bordering%20on%20the%20%E2%80%98romantic'%20in%20%3Cem%3EAparajito%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Unvanquished%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1956)%20or%20%3Cem%3EMahanagar%20%3C%2Fem%3E(1963)%2C%20has%20appealed%20to%20Bose%20as%20being%20related%20to%20history%20without%20any%20%E2%80%98violent%20ruptures%20but%20only%20lessons%20from%20the%20past%20and%20present'.%20Suman%20Ghosh%20has%2C%20however%2C%20emphatically%20argued%20that%20Ray%20instead%20stood%20%E2%80%98in%20defiance%20of%20the%20state'.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20still%20from%20Aparajito%2C%20The%20Unvanquished%C2%A0(1956)%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22A%20still%20from%20Aparajito%2C%20The%20Unvanquished%C2%A0(1956)%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-04%2Frrou414o_aparajito_625x300_07_April_25.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20still%20from%20%3Cem%3EAparajito%2C%20The%20Unvanquished%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0(1956)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20indeed%20true%2C%20as%20Jyotika%20Virdi%20cautions%2C%20that%20Ray's%20contemporary%20and%20rival%20from%20Bengal%2C%20Ritwik%20Ghatak%2C%20was%20%E2%80%98a%20superb%20filmmaker%20in%20his%20own%20right%2C%20from%20whom%20Satyajit%20Ray%2C%20many%20believe%2C%20undeservingly%20'stole%20the%20spotlight'.%20Nonetheless%2C%20as%20Ravi%20Vasudevan%20might%20elaborate%2C%20though%20Ray's%20cinema%20may%20have%20seemed%20unopposed%20to%20the%20immediate%20meaning%20of%20Nehruvian%20nation%20building%2C%20it%20never%20aligned%20with%20the%20state's%20construction%20of%20a%20coherent%20national%20identity.%20Themes%20of%20displacement%2C%20social%20dichotomy%2C%20and%20incomplete%20or%20fragmented%20modernities%20continued%20to%20punctuate%20his%20filmmaking.%20Perhaps%2C%20what%20disturbed%20Ray%20the%20most%20was%20India's%20middle-class%20nationalist%20imagination.%20This%20disturbance%20probably%20became%20most%20acute%20in%20films%20like%20%3Cem%3ESadgati%20%3C%2Fem%3E(1981)%20and%20%3Cem%3EGanashatru%20%3C%2Fem%3E(1989)%2C%20which%20were%20highly%20critical%20of%20social%20injustice%2C%20class%20inequities%2C%20and%20caste-based%20oppression.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20might%20seem%20here%20that%20the%20objective%20of%20this%20article%20has%20been%20to%20lament%20the%20lack%20of%20credit%20given%20to%20Ray%20during%20his%20life.%20It%20may%20also%20appear%20that%2C%20in%20doing%20so%2C%20the%20piece%20highlights%20the%20tension%20between%20market%20forces%20and%20artistic%20expressions.%20These%2C%20however%2C%20are%20just%20some%20weary%20costumes%20that%20this%20piece%20has%20worn%20to%20try%20to%20convey%20a%20subtler%20moral%20imperative.%20Dutt%20was%20of%20the%20view%20that%20if%20Ray's%20film%20%3Cem%3EDevi%20%3C%2Fem%3E%5Bor%20perhaps%20his%20adaptation%20of%20Henrik%20Ibsen's%3Cem%3E%20An%20Enemy%20of%20the%20People%20%3C%2Fem%3E(1882)%20in%20%3Cem%3EGanashatru%3C%2Fem%3E%5D%20had%20truly%20seeped%20into%20the%20Indian%20psyche%2C%20the%20religious%20fanaticism%20of%20the%201980s%20and%201990s%20would%20have%20perhaps%20unfolded%20differently.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Myth%20Of%20An%20'Apolitical'%20Ray%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20artists%20like%20Ray%20may%20not%20be%20the%20good-old%20realists%20that%20socialist%20regimes%20warranted%2C%20but%20poets%20in%20whom%2C%20as%20T.S.%20Eliot%20described%20in%3Cem%3E%20Tradition%20and%20the%20Individual%20Talent%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20persona%20%E2%80%9Cwho%20suffers%20and%20the%20mind%20which%20creates%E2%80%9D%20are%20distinct%20entities%3B%20such%20a%20poet%20or%20artist%20creates%20not%20by%20reproducing%20one's%20own%20experience%20but%20by%20digesting%20and%20transmuting%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20passions%20which%20are%20its%20material%E2%80%9D.%20In%20those%20transmutations%20lay%20Ray's%20challenge%20to%20the%20dominant%20ideologies%20and%20power%20structures%20that%2C%20after%20they%20had%20ignored%20him%20in%20his%20prime%2C%20sought%20to%20claim%20his%20legacy%20as%20their%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERay%20was%20not%20apolitical.%20Ironically%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20morphing%20his%20stature%20as%2020th-century%20India's%20%E2%80%98Renaissance%20Man'%20was%20a%20depoliticisation%20of%20his%20life%20-%20or%20lives%20like%20his%2C%20whose%20artistic%20genius%20has%20been%20used%20to%20mask%20India's%20social%20contradictions.%C2%A0%20The%20reader%20cannot%20be%20blamed%20for%20thinking%20that%20this%20article%20was%20written%20in%20disapproval%20of%20Ray's%20delayed%20recognition%20by%20certain%20factors%20of%20the%20Indian%20state.%20But%2C%20it%20was%20not.%20Rather%2C%20it%20was%20written%20in%20recognition%20of%20the%20fact%20that%20posthumous%20or%20highly%20belated%20recognitions%20from%20the%20state%20and%20society%20often%20seek%20to%20camouflage%20uncomfortable%20truths%20-%20truths%20that%20these%20very%20awardees%20spoke%2C%20before%20they%20were%20to%20speak%20no%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%5BArup%20K.%20Chatterjee%20is%20the%20author%20of%20'The%20Great%20Indian%20Railways'%20(2017%2C%202019)%2C%20'Indians%20in%20London'%20(2021)%2C%20and%20'Adam's%20Bridge'%20(2024)%5D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1744025100000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.ndtvimg.com%2Fmt%2Fmovies%2F2013-05%2Fray-alter.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fno-satyajit-ray-is-not-your-renaissance-man-8107786%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Often%2C%20posthumous%20or%20belated%20recognitions%20from%20the%20state%20and%20society%20seek%20to%20camouflage%20uncomfortable%20truths%20-%20truths%20that%20these%20very%20awardees%20spoke%20before%20they%20were%20to%20speak%20no%20more.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fno-satyajit-ray-is-not-your-renaissance-man-8107786%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Dozens%20die%20after%20torrential%20rain%20hammers%20Congolese%20capital%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1744024968000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F0c60%2Flive%2Ff3fd1c90-139d-11f0-b054-11b99aeb4b3e.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fcr782rgn8x4o%231%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Kinshasa%20is%20prone%20to%20soil%20erosion%20and%20the%20president%20warned%20the%20climate%20crisis%20is%20making%20flooding%20worse.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1278%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fcr782rgn8x4o%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fcr782rgn8x4o.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fcr782rgn8x4o.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22LPG%20prices%20hiked%20by%20%E2%82%B950%2Fcylinder%20for%20Ujjwala%2C%20general%20category%20customers%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22